pr_title: Redireting to dashboard on signup with limited priviledges
pr_body:
Feat: #2646 

Feature added:
1. Unregistered user on signup will now to directed to home page instead of login page.
2. Unverified user will now be able to access his/her dashboard but with limited privileges.
3. Meaningful message added to the dashboard of unverified user telling them to verify their email id in order to get all privileges.
4. Redirecting to home page after logging out.

GIF of feature:
![limited_access_to_unverified_user](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44888949/79062338-377cb300-7cb7-11ea-8347-deb04156dfd1.gif)

pr_body:
Fixes: #2698 [Add a tab for participated challenges for participants]

- [x] Added an API to fetch the participated challenges for a particular user.

- [x] Added a tab in the left sidebar to show the participated challenges for a participant.

GIF:
![ezgif com-video-to-gif](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44888949/85929880-d9369800-b8d5-11ea-812b-f8783998bd86.gif)
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 446028233, 'comment_body': "@Kajol-Kumari Instead of iterating in a loop for all challenges and then check if user has participated in a challenge, you can simply filter challenge on the basis of queries which are in the `q_params` variable and for the participant teams which are present for the current user.

In other words - you should get the participant team for the current user and then should say something like gimme all the challenges which have this participant team (inside the filter).
Let me know if I'm not clear.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 26, 7, 57, 27, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Sanji515', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 446046684, 'comment_body': 'As we are using same variable name in hosted challenges API also so do you think we should name different variable for participated challenges and the hosted challenges?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 26, 8, 34, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Sanji515', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 446064354, 'comment_body': "@Sanji515 we can name the different variables for participated and hosted challenges but i think it's fine this way also 'coz the variable will be assigned each time the required url is visited. Fixes: #2646 [Redirecting to home page with limited access after sign up]

**Changes introduced through this PR**

- [x] Permission denied component Added
 

- [x] Unverified users can view `all challenges`

Feat:#2648 
Fixed: #2664 

Features added:
1. Participant team can delete it's member.
2. Host team can delete it's member

GIF for Participant team:
![ezgif com-video-to-gif (3)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44888949/74099304-1fb67080-4b48-11ea-9ab9-78fa51c7cdff.gif)

pr_title: [#2785] Create unique URL for each phase under My Submission and All Submissions Page
pr_body:
fix: #2785 

- [x]  Added unique url using slug for `All_submissions` of a particular phase.

- [x] Add unique url for get submissions under `my_submissions` tab

- [x] Add the required tests.

GIF for feature added:
![ezgif com-video-to-gif (1)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44888949/81923480-60b49a00-95fb-11ea-8200-be5175e7f2fe.gif)
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 425556638, 'comment_body': 'Hey @Kajol-Kumari The problem is here, actually this thing is getting called before [this](https://github.com/Cloud-CV/EvalAI/blob/master/frontend/src/js/controllers/challengeCtrl.js#L505) API but in order to work as we are using `vm.phases` inside `vm.getResults` function so the above mentioned API should call first and then `vm.getResults` function should be called.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 15, 4, 15, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Sanji515', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 425572778, 'comment_body': "But @Sanji515 in the network tab i can see that [this API](https://github.com/Cloud-CV/EvalAI/blob/master/frontend/src/js/controllers/challengeCtrl.js#L504) being hit first and after that it's throwing that error of length of undefined.

Attached screenshort:
![Screenshot from 2020-05-15 10-53-13](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44888949/82014486-55fd1200-969a-11ea-9e16-bbfa439fc338.png)
", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 15, 5, 24, 33, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Kajol-Kumari', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 425581230, 'comment_body': "yes but after the execution of this(^) condition, that's reason of `vm.phases.results` is coming as `undefined`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 15, 5, 54, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Sanji515', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 425581952, 'comment_body': 'yes @Sanji515, Thanks for pointing this.I just restricted the call of `vm.getResult()` only after the value is assigned in vm.phases and now it works fine for me. Please check on your end once.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 15, 5, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Kajol-Kumari', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 425842543, 'comment_body': '@Kajol-Kumari Why there are 3 versions?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 15, 14, 31, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Sanji515', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 425843896, 'comment_body': 'As here it can be either slug or challenge phase id so can you please rename the variable to something like `challenge_phase_pk_or_slug`', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 15, 14, 34, 6, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Sanji515', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 425844810, 'comment_body': 'Same here.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 15, 14, 35, 27, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Sanji515', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 425870637, 'comment_body': '2 will be enough to serve our purpose.will remove the third one.One for `slug` based access and other for `id` based access.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 15, 15, 14, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Kajol-Kumari', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 425910876, 'comment_body': 'Can you please tell why are you doing this? pr_title: [Fix #2033] Display participant team name in my submission tab
pr_body:
Fix: #2033 [ Display participant team name by which a participant participates in a challenge in my submission tab ]
 

- [x] Add an API to fetch the participant team of the user corresponding the challenge.

 

- [x] Write tests for the API

 

- [x] Add frontend code in My Submissions Tab to display the participant team of the user for the corresponding challenge.

Screenshot:
GIF:
![team-name](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44888949/92700139-19050b80-f36c-11ea-8b2c-d53898b8ac28.gif)

New Frontend GIF:
![v2-team-name](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44888949/92700170-21f5dd00-f36c-11ea-949c-956eb926df2a.gif)


cc: @RishabhJain2018 @deshraj

pr_body:
**Changes Introduced**

- Merged `manage` and `settings` tab.

- Font weight fixed for submit page

- Edit team and add team member model improved.

- Analytics for each challenge added.

- Modal UI improved.

- Insert Image feature added in `quill-editor`

- Leaderboard UI improved.

GIF:
![GIF3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44888949/91028499-2ce60900-e61b-11ea-975f-972bc3f52669.gif)

Please correct me if i am missing something.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 2, 18, 20, 39, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Kajol-Kumari', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 386568011, 'comment_body': '@Kajol-Kumari No, sorry if I wasn't clear. I didn't want you to use that code here.
What I meant was that, instead of the whole `try except` block:
```python
    try:
        challenge_host = get_challenge_host_model(pk)
    except ChallengeHost.DoesNotExist:
        response_data = {"error": "ChallengeHost does not exist"}
        return Response(response_data, status=status.HTTP_406_NOT_ACCEPTABLE)
```
you can just do:
```python
challenge_host = get_challenge_host_model(pk)
```
I mentioned the code to show that when the function `get_model_object` is called, it itself gives a 404 error (by raising `rest_framework.NotFound`), and the except block is not reached.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 2, 18, 26, 9, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'nikochiko', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 386571146, 'comment_body': 'My mistake, i understood something else. Thanks a lot for clarifying it @nikochiko ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 2, 18, 31, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Kajol-Kumari', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_body:
Lazy loading implemented as i proposed in [GSOC'20 Ideas list](https://github.com/Cloud-CV/GSoC-Ideas/issues/28)
List of modules for which i have included lazy loading:

- [x] Auth Module
- [x] Challenge Module
- [x] Publiclist Module

List of modules for which Refactoring is Done :

-  [x] Auth Module
-  [x] Challenge Module 
-  [x] Dashboard Module
-  [x] Home Module
-  [x] Nav Module
-  [x] Publiclist Module
-  [x] Utility Module

Work left to be done:
- [ ] Certain enhancement is required, like these modules can be further divided into sub-modules to further improve the performance of the site.

pr_title: Tabs added to challenge list page
pr_body:
Features Added:
1. Challenge list page will now contains three tabs for navigation between ongoing,upcoming and completed challenges.
2. The navigation tab content also contain the total count of challenge of a particular type.

pr_title: Check for maximum allowed submissions added
pr_body:
Fixes: #180 [ Add a check while editing phase details in challenge page ]

Changes proposed:

The host will be notified and will not be able to edit the maximum_allowed_submissions field if the given input doesn't satisfy the condition `maximum_submissions_per_day > maximum_submissions_per_month > maximum_total_submissions`

GIF showing the added Check on maximum_allowed_submissions:
![ezgif com-video-to-gif](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44888949/82801383-d988e100-9e9a-11ea-91fe-1aa1b3a57580.gif)
